snippet.textDisplay: Great review! I have one of the originals and have been happy with it. I wish it the Tesla powertrain with the Fisker exterior design.  Great car to drive- very smooth and comfortable with decent acceleration (but not Tesla-like).  Luxurious is a good word for it.  Considering the company went under, the service has not been an issue (I have a former tech who comes to my home to service it annually).  The later the VIN the better (mine is a later one - the early ones had some battery issues).   Trying to figure out whether to keep it (will it increase in value over time?) or sell it to make room in the collection.
